@startuml
title Use Case 1: Logging In

actor User
boundary GUI as "Client GUI"
control Client as "Client App"
control Server as "Server"
collections Cache as "Server Cache\n(User data + Conversation headers)"

== Startup ==
User -> GUI: Open program
GUI -> Client: Launch / initialize
Client -> Server: Connect()

alt Cannot connect to server
Server --> Client: Connection failed
Client -> GUI: Show error message\n"Cannot connect to server"
else Connected
Server --> Client: Connection established
Client -> GUI: Display Login Page
end

== Authentication ==
loop Until valid credentials or user cancels
User -> GUI: Enter username/password\nClick "Login"
GUI -> Client: Submit credentials
Client -> Server: Authenticate(credentials)

Server -> Cache: Verify credentials\n(username/password hash)
alt Invalid credentials
Cache --> Server: No match / invalid password
Server --> Client: Auth failed
Client -> GUI: Show "Invalid login"\nAllow retry
else Valid credentials
Cache --> Server: User found + role
Server -> Cache: Get user profile data
Server -> Cache: Get conversation headers\n(conversation IDs + participants)
Cache --> Server: User data + conversation headers
Server --> Client: Auth success\n(user data, conv headers, role)

Client -> GUI: Load user data\nPopulate conversation list

alt Regular user
Client -> GUI: Open Regular Mode UI
else IT user
Client -> GUI: Open IT Mode UI
end
break
end
end
@enduml
